==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guinea-pig director
<hw>Guin"ea-pig` di*rec"tor</hw>. <def>A director (usually one holding a
number of directorships) who serves merely or mainly for the fee (in
England, often a guinea) paid for attendance.</def>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guinness</ent>⟦br⟧
